Gold Declines for Second Day After Libya Gets Venezuelan Mediation Offer

-- B y   W e n d y   P u g h
-- 
2011-03-03T23:29:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/gold-declines-for-second-day-after-libya-gets-venezuelan-mediation-offer.html
Gold for immediate delivery declined
0.2 percent to $1,413.65 an ounce at 10:25 a.m. Melbourne time.
The metal slumped as much as 1.7 percent yesterday after
Venezuela offered to mediate a resolution to the crisis in  Libya .  Gold for April delivery in  New York  fell 0.1 percent to
$1,415.30 after earlier advancing to $1,416.90.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Pugh in Melbourne at 
